Love me some Commander gameplay, but really not a fan of Commander Vs. overall. Not as much quality as Command Zone or MTG Muddstah, and more fluff to filter through than either.
I really enjoy it because it’s a bunch of friends sitting down to play fun and silly versions of decks.
Nothing’s going to match Command Zone for production quality so it’s a bit of an unfair comparison, but I certainly wouldn’t put Muddstah above them.
I do like the more casual feel, but at the same time I really dislike the dilly dallying before, after, and during gameplay.
For sure nothing will compare with that Command Zone money
though
That’s what fast forward’s for...you aren’t held captive of the other parts of the show.
Also JLK is an actual trained professional.
Muddstah is the best
I still think Lexicon has the best tech
I really like Muddstah, although I will say that it makes for terrible background noise.
If you aren't actively paying attention, you'll have no idea what's going on in seconds.
You may enjoy Muddstah’s condensing, but I wouldn’t put it as the best.
And I agree with <@U4V5EHQ2G> that Lexicon’s setup is very good, though there it’s also tough to know which cards are being played.

It’s the best for me because I enjoy his content the most/ it’s how I want to consume Commander content. 
Translated my hyperbole.
I miss the social/political aspect from Muddstah since it’s just condensed gameplay.
I really enjoy that from Cmdr Vs.
